### Main API (Port 3000)

# Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health HTTP/1.1

###
GET http://localhost:3000/ready HTTP/1.1

# ==================== Users Endpoints ====================

### Get all users
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users HTTP/1.1

### Get user by ID
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/1 HTTP/1.1

### Create user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Johnson",
  "email": "alice@example.com"
}

### Update user
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/users/1 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Updated",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com"
}

### Partially update user
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/users/1 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Partially Updated"
}

### Delete user
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/users/1 HTTP/1.1

# ==================== Roles Endpoints ====================

### Get all roles
GET http://localhost:3000/api/roles HTTP/1.1

### Get role by ID
GET http://localhost:3000/api/roles/1 HTTP/1.1

### Create role
POST http://localhost:3000/api/roles HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Moderator",
  "description": "Can moderate content",
  "permissions": ["read", "write", "moderate"]
}

### Update role
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/roles/1 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin Updated",
  "description": "Updated administrator role",
  "permissions": ["read", "write", "delete", "manage"]
}

### Partially update role
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/roles/1 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "permissions": ["read", "write", "delete"]
}

### Delete role
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/roles/1 HTTP/1.1


### ==================== ADMIN API (Port 3001) ====================

# Admin Health Check
GET http://localhost:3001/health HTTP/1.1

###
GET http://localhost:3001/ready HTTP/1.1

# ==================== Admin User Management ====================

### Get all users (admin view with extra details)
GET http://localhost:3001/admin/users HTTP/1.1

### Get user by ID (admin view)
GET http://localhost:3001/admin/users/1 HTTP/1.1

### Suspend user account
POST http://localhost:3001/admin/users/1/suspend HTTP/1.1

### Activate suspended user account
POST http://localhost:3001/admin/users/1/activate HTTP/1.1

### Create user (admin)
POST http://localhost:3001/admin/users HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin Created User",
  "email": "admin.user@example.com"
}

### Update user (admin)
PUT http://localhost:3001/admin/users/1 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin Updated User",
  "email": "admin.updated@example.com"
}

### Delete user (admin)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/admin/users/1 HTTP/1.1

# ==================== Admin Role Management ====================

### Get all roles (admin view)
GET http://localhost:3001/admin/roles HTTP/1.1

### Get role by ID (admin view)
GET http://localhost:3001/admin/roles/1 HTTP/1.1

### Remove role from user
DELETE http://localhost:3001/admin/roles/1/users/2 HTTP/1.1

### Create role (admin)
POST http://localhost:3001/admin/roles HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "SuperAdmin",
  "description": "Super administrator with all permissions",
  "permissions": ["all"]
}

### Update role (admin)
PUT http://localhost:3001/admin/roles/1 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin Role Updated",
  "description": "Updated admin role",
  "permissions": ["all", "system"]
}
}

### Delete role (admin)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/admin/roles/1 HTTP/1.1

# ==================== Admin System Management ====================

### Get system statistics
GET http://localhost:3001/admin/system/stats HTTP/1.1

### Get system configuration
GET http://localhost:3001/admin/system/config HTTP/1.1

### Clear application cache
POST http://localhost:3001/admin/system/cache/clear HTTP/1.1
